## Implementation Summary

### What was built
Since all engine dependencies (issues #11–#26) were still open, the entire Cycle 2 game engine was implemented first using TDD, then the property-based tests.

**Engine modules (14 files):**
- `state.py` — `Player`, `PropertyOwnership`, `GameState` models
- `rent.py` — Pure rent calculator (monopoly bonus, houses/hotels, railroads, utilities)
- `jail.py` — Jail mechanics (PAY_FINE, USE_GOOJF, ROLL_DOUBLES with 3-attempt limit)
- `effects.py` — Card effect executor (all 10 `CardEffect` variants)
- `purchase.py` — Strategy-delegated property purchase
- `buildings.py` — House/hotel building with even-build rule and supply limits (32/12)
- `mortgage.py` — Mortgage/unmortgage with 10% interest
- `bankruptcy.py` — Forced liquidation and asset transfer
- `turn.py` — Full turn resolution (movement, Go salary, tax, cards, rent)
- `game.py` — Game loop orchestrator with doubles re-rolls and building phase
- `strategies/` — 6 strategy implementations: BuyEverything, BuyNothing, ColorTargeted, ThreeHousesRush, JailCamper, Trader

**Test file deliverable:** `tests/test_game_invariants.py` with 20 tests (5 Hypothesis property-based + 15 integration tests)

### Results
- **359 tests, 0 failures**
- **95% aggregate coverage** (requirement: ≥90% ✅)
- All acceptance criteria satisfied
